label: PROCESSOR
description: This field identifies the check order processor.

label: RECORDCHANGEDATE
description: This field stores the system date when you create, change, or save the Check Order record.

label: USERID
description: This field stores the user number of the person who creates the Check Order record.

label: STATUS
description: This field indicates the current status of the check order.

label: STATUSDATE
description: This field stores the date when you changed the value in the Status field.

label: OPENDATE
description: This field stores the date the Check Order record was created.

label: LASTORDERDATE
description: This field stores the date a check order was last sent to the processor.

label: LASTFREEORDER
description: This field records the date for a free or promotional check order.

label: MICRLINE
description: This field stores the information to be imprinted magnetically on the MICR line at the bottom of the check.

label: STARTNUMBER
description: This fields stores either the starting check number for new orders or the starting reorder number.

label: QUANTITY
description: This field specifies the number of checks being ordered.

label: CHECKTYPE
description: This field specifies the type of checks being ordered

label: CHECKSTYLE
description: This field specifies the style of checks being ordered.

label: COVERSTYLE
description: This field specifies the style of the checkbook cover.

label: CUTNUMBER
description: This field is used by Clarke American, Harland, and Deluxe only, and it specifies the style of the cut (insignia) on the checks.

label: COVERINITIALS
description: This field is used by Clarke American and Harland only, and it specifies the initials, if any, to be imprinted on the checkbook cover.

label: CHECKINITIALS
description: This field is used by Clarke American only, and it specifies the initials, if any, to be imprinted on the checks.

label: BRANCH
description: This field stores a processor-assigned code that identifies your credit union.

label: IMPRINTLINE:1
description: This field specifies the first line of name or address information to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTLINE:2
description: This field specifies the second line of name or address information to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTLINE:3
description: This field specifies the third line of name or address information to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTLINE:4
description: This field specifies the fourth line of name or address information to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTLINE:5
description: This field specifies the fifth line of name or address information to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTLINE:6
description: This field specifies the sixth line of name or address information to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTCITY
description: This field is used by Clarke American only, and it specifies the name of the city to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTSTATE
description: This field is used by Clarke American only, and it specifies the two-character U.S. Postal Service state code to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTZIPCODE
description: This field is used by Clarke American and Deluxe only, and it specifies the ZIP Code to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTPHONE
description: This field is used by Clarke American and Deluxe only, and it specifies the telephone number to be imprinted on the checks.

label: IMPRINTFONT
description: This field specifies the font for the imprint lines.

label: IMPRINTJUSTIFY
description: This field is used by Clarke American, Harland, and Liberty only, and it specifies the justification (alignment) of the imprint lines.

label: MAILADDRESS:1–MAILADDRESS:5
description: These fields specify the mailing address for the check order.

label: MAILCITY
description: This field is used by Clarke American only, and it specifies the name of the city to which the check order should be mailed.

label: MAILSTATE
description: This field is used by Clarke American only, and it specifies the two-character U.S. Postal Code for the state to which the check order should be mailed.

label: MAILZIPCODE
description: This field is used by Clarke American and Harland only, and it specifies the ZIP Code the check order should be mailed to.

label: BILLINGCODE
description: This field specifies how the check order should be billed.

label: SHIPMETHOD
description: This field specifies how the check order should be shipped.

label: SHIPTO
description: This field is used by Clarke American, Deluxe, and Liberty only, and it specifies to whom the check order should be shipped.

label: OVERSIGFONT
description: This field is used by Clarke American, Harland, and Liberty only, and it specifies the font style for the Over Signature Line 1 and Over Signature Line 2 fields.

label: OVERSIGJUSTIFY
description: This field is used by Clarke American and Harland only, and it specifies the alignment for the over signature lines.

label: OVERSIGLINESIZE
description: This field is used by Harland only, and it specifies the font size for the over signature lines.

label: OVERSIGLINE:1
description: This field specifies the information to be imprinted on the first line of text, over the signature line (or signature lines).

label: OVERSIGLINE:2
description: This field specifies the information to be imprinted on the second line of text, over the signature line (or signature lines).

label: SPECIALINSTR:1
description: This field stores a line of special instructions for the processor.

label: SPECIALINSTR:2
description: This field is used by Clarke American, Deluxe, and Liberty only, and it stores a second line of special instructions.

label: SPECIALINSTR:3
description: These fields are used by Deluxe only, and they store the third through eighth lines of special instructions.

label: SPECIALINSTR:4
description: These fields are used by Deluxe only, and they store the third through eighth lines of special instructions.

label: SPECIALINSTR:5
description: These fields are used by Deluxe only, and they store the third through eighth lines of special instructions.

label: SPECIALINSTR:6
description: These fields are used by Deluxe only, and they store the third through eighth lines of special instructions.

label: SPECIALINSTR:7
description: These fields are used by Deluxe only, and they store the third through eighth lines of special instructions.

label: SPECIALINSTR:8
description: These fields are used by Deluxe only, and they store the third through eighth lines of special instructions.

label: PROMONUMBER
description: This field is used by Clarke America, Harland, and Deluxe only, and it stores a promo number.

label: LASTFMDATE
description: This field stores the date of the last file maintenance of this Check Order record.

label: NUMBERSIGLINES
description: This field specifies the number of signature lines to be included on the checks.

label: SSN:1
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the Social Security Number or individual Taxpayer Identification Number to be imprinted on checks.

label: SSN:2
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the second Social Security Number or individual Taxpayer Identification Number to be imprinted on checks.

label: LICENSE:1
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the license number to imprint on the checks.

label: LICENSE:2
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies a second license number to be imprinted on the checks.

label: BINDING
description: This field is not currently used.

label: DESIGN
description: This field is not currently used.

label: BUSINESSSERIAL
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the serial letters to be imprinted after the check number on the business checks.

label: BUSNUMCOPIES
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it indicates the number of carbonless check copies required (in addition to the original check) for business checks.

label: BUSBINDINGSTYLE
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the binding style of the checkbook for business checks.

label: BUSVOUCHERNUMBER
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it indicates the voucher number that designates the purpose of the checks.

label: BUSCAPTIONS:1
description: These fields are used by Deluxe only, and they specify a deduction caption to be imprinted on business checks.

label: ACCTADDRINKCOLOR
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the ink color for the account and address information imprinted on the business checks.

label: TITLEINKCOLOR
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the ink color used for the title plate for business checks.

label: CUTINKCOLOR
description: This field is used by Deluxe only, and it specifies the ink color used for the cut (insignia) for business checks.

label: TAXEXEMPTCODE
description: This field is used by Harland only, and it specifies whether the check order is tax-exempt.

label: RERUNREASON
description: This field is used by Harland only, and it specifies the reason a check order must be rerun.

label: PONUMBER

label: CHARGESHIPPING

label: IMPRINTUSAGE:1

label: ACCENT
description: This field is used by Liberty only, and it specifies the accent figure printed to the left of the name.

label: PHANTOM
description: This field is used by Liberty only, and it specifies the phantom figure printed in the center of the checks.

label: SIGFIGURE
description: This field is used by Liberty only, and it specifies the signature figure printed next to the signature line.

label: LOCATOR
description: This field value in each record is unique for each member account.
